# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.

## Commands

```bash
# Development
yarn dev                    # Start dev server on http://localhost:3000

# Database
yarn db:migrate             # Run migrations
yarn db:migrate:down        # Rollback last migration
yarn db:migrate:make <name> # Create new migration
yarn db:seed                # Run all seeds (server/db/seeds)
yarn db:seed:make <name>    # Create new seed file
yarn db:codegen             # Generate TypeScript types from database

# Testing
yarn test                   # Run backend tests in watch mode (server/**/*.test.ts)
yarn test:run               # Run backend tests once
yarn test:frontend          # Run frontend tests in watch mode (app/**/*.test.ts)
yarn test:frontend:run      # Run frontend tests once
yarn typecheck              # Run TypeScript type checking
yarn lint                   # Run oxlint (linter)
yarn lint:fix               # Run oxlint with auto-fix
yarn fmt                    # Format code with oxfmt
yarn fmt:check              # Check formatting without writing

# Build
yarn build                  # Production build
```

**Environment:** Set `NUXT_DATABASE_URL` for PostgreSQL connection (auto-binds to `runtimeConfig.databaseUrl`).

## Architecture

### Nuxt 4 Structure
- `app/` - Frontend (pages, components, assets)
- `server/` - Backend (API handlers, database, test utilities)
- `src/volt/` - Volt UI components (PrimeVue unstyled + Tailwind)

### UI Components (Volt)
Volt components are PrimeVue unstyled components with Tailwind styling. Registered with `Volt` prefix via nuxt.config.ts.

**Customization:** Use `pt:section:class` syntax for pass-through styling:
```vue
<VoltButton pt:root:class="bg-zinc-900 hover:bg-zinc-800" />
<VoltCard pt:root:class="rounded-2xl" pt:body:class="p-6" />
```

Available: VoltAvatar, VoltButton, VoltCard, VoltConfirmDialog, VoltDataTable, VoltDatePicker, VoltDialog, VoltInputMask, VoltInputText, VoltMessage, VoltMultiSelect, VoltPassword, VoltSecondaryButton, VoltSelect, VoltTag, VoltTextarea, VoltToast

### Database (Kysely + PostgreSQL)
- `server/utils/db.ts` - Database connection, exports `db` and `useDatabase()`
- `server/db/migrations/` - Kysely migrations
- `server/db/factories.ts` - Row builders shared by tests AND seeds (`DbLike` type)
- `server/db/seeds/` - Seed files (run via `yarn db:seed`)
- `server/db/db.d.ts` - Auto-generated types (via `yarn db:codegen`)
- `kysely.config.ts` - Migration + seed configuration

### Seeds (Convention)
Seeds populate a preview/dev DB with the minimum needed to log in and work.

- **Shared factories**: seeds and tests import the same row builders from
  `server/db/factories.ts`. Tests pass a rolled-back `Transaction`; seeds pass a
  live `Kysely` connection. Uniqueness rides a monotonic `nextSeq()` counter.
- **Order-independent + idempotent by contract**: `kysely seed:run` runs every
  file in `readdir` order with no ledger, so a seed must not depend on another
  having run, and re-running must not throw or duplicate. Rows that must be
  *stable and addressable* (the anchor login user) upsert on a natural key.
- **Validity harness**: `server/db/seeds.harness.test.ts` runs every seed against
  the latest migration and twice-over, catching constraint drift and
  non-idempotency that typecheck can't see.

### Preview / Dev Login
A preview box serves on a dynamic URL that can't be a Google OAuth redirect URI,
so it logs in via a dev-only backdoor instead:

- `server/utils/preview.ts` - `PREVIEW_ANCHOR_USER` (single source of truth, also
  seeded by `server/db/seeds`). Edit it to rebrand the anchor user.
- `server/api/auth/preview-login.get.ts` - establishes a session as that user.
  Double-gated on `import.meta.dev` (compile-time, dead in prod builds) **and**
  `NUXT_PREVIEW_MODE` (runtime). The `/login` button only appears when the
  matching `public.previewMode` runtime flag is on.

### Backend Testing (Transaction Rollback Pattern)
Tests use real PostgreSQL with automatic transaction rollback for isolation.

```typescript
import { test, expect, mockGet, mockPost, expectHttpError } from "~/server/test-utils";
import handler from "./index.get";

test("returns users", async ({ factories }) => {
  await factories.user({ email: "alice@example.com", first_name: "Alice", last_name: "Smith" });
  const event = mockGet();
  const result = await handler(event);
  expect(result).toHaveLength(1);
});
```

- `factories` fixture creates test data within transaction
- Always destructure `factories` even if unused (sets up transaction)
- Mock helpers: `mockGet()`, `mockPost()`, `mockPut()`, `mockDelete()`
- `expectHttpError(fn, statusCode)` - Assert handler throws HTTP error

### API Handler Pattern
```typescript
import { z } from "zod";

export default defineEventHandler(async (event) => {
  const db = useDatabase();
  const body = await readBody(event);
  // ... validation with zod, database operations
});
```

## Design System

See `DESIGN_LANGUAGE.md` for the complete design system. Key points:

- **Zinc-first palette** - Use zinc for almost everything
- **Semantic colors only** - Emerald for success, red for danger
- **No decorative shadows** - Only on hover for interactivity
- **Icons** - PrimeIcons (`pi pi-*` classes)

## Agent Skills

This project depends on `@gallopsystems/agent-skills`, which symlinks Claude Code
skills into `.claude/skills/` on every `yarn install`. Check there before solving
a problem from scratch — the skills that matter here:

- `kysely-postgres` - query patterns, migrations, type generation
- `nuxt-nitro-api` - API handlers, validation, auth, SSR
- `nitro-testing` - the transaction-rollback test harness used in this repo
- `git-github` - branch/PR workflow, debugging failed Actions runs
- `doctl` - DigitalOcean deployments and logs
- `copier-template` - applying template updates (see below)

If `.claude/skills/` is missing, run `yarn install`. To pick up newer skills:
`yarn up @gallopsystems/agent-skills`.

**Contribute lessons back:** if you work through an error, gotcha, or workflow
knot that no installed skill covers (or one contradicts), offer to upstream it:
"Want me to contribute this back to the skills repo?" If yes, run
`/contribute-skill`.

## Template Updates

This project was scaffolded from [gallop-systems/nuxt-copier-template](https://github.com/gallop-systems/nuxt-copier-template). The version it's on is recorded in `.copier-answers.yml` (`_commit`) — never edit that file by hand.

To apply an update, follow the `copier-template` skill (`applying-updates.md` has the full conflict-resolution procedure). The short version:

```bash
git checkout chore/template-update && git pull
uvx copier update --trust --defaults

# resolve conflict markers and *.rej files, then validate
yarn install && yarn typecheck && yarn lint && yarn fmt:check && yarn test:run

git add -A   # must include .copier-answers.yml
git commit -m "chore: update to template vX.Y.Z"
git push
```
